.TH "spmi_ext_register_write" 9 "spmi_ext_register_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spmi_ext_register_write \- extended register write
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" spmi_ext_register_write
.BI "(struct spmi_device *sdev "  ","
.BI "u8 addr "  ","
.BI "const u8 *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdev" 12
SPMI device.
.IP "addr" 12
slave register address (8-bit address).
.IP "buf" 12
buffer containing the data to be transferred to the Slave.
.IP "len" 12
the request number of bytes to read (up to 16 bytes).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Writes up to 16 bytes of data to the extended register space of a
Slave device.
